headline: UPS (UPS): Assessing Valuation After New Labor Settlements Reduce Strike Risk
summary: If you are weighing your next move on United Parcel Service (UPS), the latest chapter in its labor relations saga could reshape your view. After the International Brotherhood of Teamsters authorized credible strike threats targeting multiple UPS hubs, negotiations ended with settlements on a wide set of grievances. These agreements secured new contracts for several groups of workers and resolved long-standing disputes about workplace safety and job duties. This resolution reduces the risk of...
